	Rule: groovy
	------
	Otavio R. Piske
	------
	Fev, 2013
	
Description

	Executes a {{{http://groovy.codehaus.org/}Groovy}} script. The script must 
have a startup method such as this:
 
----------------------------------------
def public void start() {
	println "Groovy works!"
}
----------------------------------------
	
Element 

	Name: copy

Attributes

	file: the script to execute
	
Example

----------------------------------------
<groovy file="${workdir}/hello.groovy" />
----------------------------------------
	